1
00:01:02,007 --> 00:01:06,012
BLACK BREAD

2
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:22,928
Culet.

3
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:25,328
Culet.

4
00:04:31,647 --> 00:04:34,014
Pitorliua...

5
00:05:04,487 --> 00:05:05,773
Pauleta.

6
00:05:07,447 --> 00:05:08,892
Pauleta.

7
00:05:09,047 --> 00:05:10,014
What?

8
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:12,734
Dionis' wagon fell down
into the woods.

9
00:05:12,887 --> 00:05:14,298
What are you talking about?

10
00:05:15,807 --> 00:05:16,808
And Culet?

11
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:19,174
They're on the ground.
They look dead.

12
00:05:24,047 --> 00:05:26,698
- Where are they?
- Just around the Pallera.

13
00:05:32,887 --> 00:05:35,367
As you sow, so shall you reap.

14
00:05:38,527 --> 00:05:40,529
- How are you?
- OK.

15
00:05:40,687 --> 00:05:43,930
We're going straight home.
Your mother's very worried.

16
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,607
Farriol, wait!

17
00:05:51,927 --> 00:05:54,328
Here!
Stop by the garrison tomorrow.

18
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:57,377
The Mayor and Judge will take
the boy's statement.

19
00:05:57,807 --> 00:05:59,457
He's been very good.

20
00:06:01,087 --> 00:06:02,498
Paperwork, you know?

21
00:06:03,087 --> 00:06:05,215
Today there's no end to paperwork.

22
00:06:09,727 --> 00:06:11,695
- You shouldn't have stopped!
- But dad...

23
00:06:11,847 --> 00:06:15,056
Don't dad me, you'll see
the headaches we have now.

24
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:22,807
Go on in!

25
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:24,093
So? What happened?

26
00:06:24,247 --> 00:06:26,249
They say a landslide accident.

27
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:29,933
My God! What a sad death!

28
00:06:30,087 --> 00:06:33,728
And poor Culet didn't have time
to even start his life.

29
00:06:34,047 --> 00:06:36,015
The woods are cursed since the war.

30
00:06:36,167 --> 00:06:37,248
Florència!

31
00:06:37,407 --> 00:06:39,136
Don't scare the boy even more!

32
00:06:57,527 --> 00:07:00,212
Dad, should I put the clothespin on?

33
00:07:01,487 --> 00:07:02,932
- Dad?
- What?

34
00:07:03,087 --> 00:07:05,897
The clothespin. They always
knock the food over.

35
00:07:06,047 --> 00:07:08,778
You notice everything, don't you?
Put it on.

36
00:07:11,007 --> 00:07:14,728
And Culet and his dad's birds?
Who'll take care of them now?

37
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:20,211
Pauleta, I guess.
Problem's who'll take care of her.

38
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:21,693
Andreu!

39
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,377
Andreu!
Come on, you'll be late for school.

40
00:07:25,527 --> 00:07:28,098
We have to go see
the Mayor and Capt. Clotet.

41
00:07:28,247 --> 00:07:31,137
I can't wait.
I should be at the factory already.

42
00:07:32,807 --> 00:07:35,048
- Who signs, him or me?
- Both.

43
00:07:35,207 --> 00:07:35,856
Andreu.

44
00:07:46,527 --> 00:07:48,894
This is everything you told us.

45
00:07:50,087 --> 00:07:51,930
You can write your own name,
can't you?

46
00:07:52,087 --> 00:07:53,737
If you're such a good student...

47
00:07:54,087 --> 00:07:54,815
Sign it.

48
00:08:14,527 --> 00:08:15,767
Poor woman.

49
00:08:16,487 --> 00:08:17,648
Andreu,

50
00:08:18,327 --> 00:08:22,218
here it says the boy wasn't dead
when you found him.

51
00:08:22,367 --> 00:08:24,369
- He didn't have time to say anything?
- No.

52
00:08:24,527 --> 00:08:27,337
A name, anything...
It could be important to us.

53
00:08:28,127 --> 00:08:32,132
Well... he said something weird.
I think it was Pitorliua.

54
00:08:33,327 --> 00:08:35,409
Does that mean anything to you?

55
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:38,332
There's a bird named that.
A little, tame one.

56
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:41,338
Yes, yes, but besides the bird?

57
00:08:43,287 --> 00:08:47,770
They say in the Baumes cave
there's like a ghost called Pitorliua.

58
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:53,488
Take the boy to the other room,
give him a coffee, he's been good.

59
00:08:53,647 --> 00:08:56,048
And you wait, we're not done yet.

60
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:59,410
Though it looks like an accident,
it's hard to believe.

61
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:03,056
We think someone
pushed Dionis Segui off.

62
00:09:03,207 --> 00:09:05,255
Children's fantasies apart,

63
00:09:05,407 --> 00:09:08,172
all that makes us think about
this Pitorliua story.

64
00:09:09,607 --> 00:09:11,609
Don't worry about a thing, kid.

65
00:09:11,767 --> 00:09:13,292
What did you say?

66
00:09:13,847 --> 00:09:15,770
Don't worry about a thing.

67
00:09:17,447 --> 00:09:19,575
We'll bring you some breakfast.

68
00:09:43,767 --> 00:09:46,418
The white bread's not for you.
Take the other one.

69
00:09:49,647 --> 00:09:51,729
You and Dionis were inseparable.

70
00:09:51,887 --> 00:09:53,730
Too much business together:

71
00:09:53,887 --> 00:09:55,696
Birds, trade unions,

72
00:09:55,847 --> 00:09:58,930
dirty work
that's better not to discuss...

73
00:09:59,327 --> 00:10:01,091
I'd be careful if I was you.

74
00:10:01,407 --> 00:10:03,250
Too many people have it in for you.

75
00:10:03,407 --> 00:10:04,897
Done lecturing me?

76
00:10:05,687 --> 00:10:09,453
I just want to warn you. There are
still a lot of reds to purge.

77
00:10:09,607 --> 00:10:11,814
You wouldn't want
to wind up like Dionis.

78
00:10:12,407 --> 00:10:14,136
Not for you,

79
00:10:14,287 --> 00:10:16,972
for the kids and widows
who never meddled.

80
00:10:19,727 --> 00:10:20,888
Andreu.

81
00:10:21,207 --> 00:10:23,892
Andreu, come on,
leave it, we're going.

82
00:10:24,287 --> 00:10:27,655
You're different from your dad.
I hope you pick a better path.

83
00:10:27,807 --> 00:10:30,458
He'll do what we want.
You have no damn say in it!

84
00:10:30,607 --> 00:10:32,371
Florència didn't choose so well.

85
00:10:32,527 --> 00:10:35,736
- So she should've chosen you!
- She'd be much better off.

86
00:10:39,927 --> 00:10:42,692
Those clowns, a bunch of losers!

87
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,334
What are you doing?

88
00:11:06,287 --> 00:11:07,812
Packing, can't you see?

89
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:09,298
Where are you going?

90
00:11:09,447 --> 00:11:10,653
To France.

91
00:11:11,527 --> 00:11:14,053
The Captain suspects
Dionis Segui was killed.

92
00:11:14,207 --> 00:11:15,652
What? Who was it?

93
00:11:15,807 --> 00:11:17,650
I don't know.
Could've been anyone.

94
00:11:17,807 --> 00:11:21,209
Even one of those Town Hall traitors.
I'm afraid they'll go after me.

95
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:22,493
But why?

96
00:11:22,647 --> 00:11:24,934
Because Dionis and I
represented too much.

97
00:11:25,087 --> 00:11:27,215
You shouldn't have gotten
into politics.

98
00:11:27,367 --> 00:11:28,937
I was defending my ideas.

99
00:11:29,087 --> 00:11:30,691
And look where you ideas got us.

100
00:11:30,847 --> 00:11:32,372
Me, I work like crazy.

101
00:11:32,527 --> 00:11:35,053
Look what you got with
your bird mania and ideals.

102
00:11:35,207 --> 00:11:38,689
All I've ever done was so
you'd never lack anything at home.

103
00:11:38,847 --> 00:11:40,372
And now too.

104
00:11:40,847 --> 00:11:43,009
I'll talk to the owners
of mother's farm

105
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:44,657
to see if they can help you.

106
00:11:44,807 --> 00:11:48,653
Those Manubens'! They ruin
everything they touch in town.

107
00:11:49,367 --> 00:11:51,256
Are you forgetting Pitorliua's mishap?

108
00:11:51,407 --> 00:11:52,568
Goddamn it!

109
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:56,574
With you always reminding me?
You can't get it out of your head.

110
00:11:56,727 --> 00:11:59,173
I'm sick of hearing it.
I'm leaving and that's it!

111
00:12:02,287 --> 00:12:04,654
If you walk out that door

112
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:06,457
I'll kill all your birds.

113
00:12:06,607 --> 00:12:09,133
Because I won't go up
to give them anything.

114
00:12:09,287 --> 00:12:11,289
No water, no millet,
no seeds, nothing!

115
00:12:11,447 --> 00:12:14,690
Just one dead bird,
and pay close attention, Florència,

116
00:12:14,847 --> 00:12:17,691
just one and you'll remember it
the rest of your life.

117
00:12:17,847 --> 00:12:18,928
Get out!

118
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,895
I'm sorry. Don't take it like that.

119
00:12:22,047 --> 00:12:23,048
I said get out!

120
00:12:33,607 --> 00:12:36,213
Can't you see I love you
more than anything?

121
00:12:40,527 --> 00:12:41,494
Come on,

122
00:12:42,047 --> 00:12:44,049
don't make it harder for me.

123
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:13,613
There's a bundle in the wagon
with everything you might need.

124
00:13:14,087 --> 00:13:17,375
I've got lots of work
and can't be there for you.

125
00:13:18,007 --> 00:13:19,850
You'll have fun at grandma's.

126
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:22,817
Playing with Quirze and Nuria.
She's here visiting.

127
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:23,934
Nuria who?

128
00:13:24,087 --> 00:13:26,169
Uncle Fonso's girl. He went to France.

129
00:13:26,327 --> 00:13:28,136
Careful on the stairs, Andreu.

130
00:13:59,487 --> 00:14:00,648
Go sit down.

131
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:04,653
Wait for me here.

132
00:14:06,407 --> 00:14:07,454
I'll be right back.

133
00:14:40,007 --> 00:14:43,295
Here, that's for grandma
to make herself a suit.

134
00:14:44,407 --> 00:14:47,331
Be good at your new school
and study a lot.

135
00:14:47,487 --> 00:14:49,649
So you don't end up
in some shitty factory.

136
00:14:49,807 --> 00:14:51,536
It's enough for me to be in one.

137
00:14:51,927 --> 00:14:53,850
I'll go see you every Sunday.

138
00:14:54,007 --> 00:14:56,453
I can't more often,
it's many hours away.

139
00:14:57,527 --> 00:14:59,336
Your father must leave,

140
00:15:00,087 --> 00:15:01,737
but he loves us.

141
00:15:05,127 --> 00:15:06,538
Don't forget that.

142
00:15:07,447 --> 00:15:10,098
You have to be a man now and bear it.

143
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:14,376
What will you do in France?

144
00:15:15,127 --> 00:15:18,210
I don't know.
Go see uncle Fonso and then we'll see.

145
00:15:18,847 --> 00:15:21,088
Don't worry, I'll be back soon.

146
00:15:21,607 --> 00:15:23,416
Then you'll come with me.

147
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:26,810
Father, does Pitorliua
from the cave really exist?

148
00:15:27,047 --> 00:15:28,458
That's just silly!

149
00:15:28,607 --> 00:15:31,577
Couldn't that be who killed
Culet and his father?

150
00:15:31,727 --> 00:15:34,378
How can you be so grown up
and believe in ghosts?

151
00:15:34,527 --> 00:15:37,497
And the screams factory workers hear
from the Baumes cave?

152
00:15:37,647 --> 00:15:39,934
Nonsense! Don't try to learn so much

153
00:15:40,087 --> 00:15:42,931
or you'll go blind like
that king in grandma's tale.

154
00:15:44,287 --> 00:15:45,493
Take the reins.

155
00:15:50,727 --> 00:15:53,128
Look, Andreu,
Pitorliua was a guy

156
00:15:53,287 --> 00:15:56,177
who hid in the Baumes
for political reasons.

157
00:15:56,327 --> 00:15:58,216
No ghosts, no stories. OK?

158
00:15:58,367 --> 00:15:59,778
Yes, father.

159
00:15:59,927 --> 00:16:03,374
- Can I have your glasses?
- No, glasses aren't to play with.

160
00:16:05,487 --> 00:16:06,693
OK, here.

161
00:16:11,447 --> 00:16:12,778
You just be well.

162
00:16:12,927 --> 00:16:16,010
That's the only obligation
kids should have.

163
00:16:20,327 --> 00:16:23,888
The kids are coming down for school.
They shouldn't see you.

164
00:16:24,047 --> 00:16:26,732
Here, take this too.
Come, let's go, mother.

165
00:16:31,007 --> 00:16:33,613
Oh, Cio! First Bernat's death,

166
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:37,328
then your husband;
Fonso lost up in France

167
00:16:37,487 --> 00:16:39,808
and now Farriol,
the only son I had left...

168
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:41,571
Farriol, what a scatterbrain!

169
00:16:41,727 --> 00:16:44,094
We need men, not more
children and headaches.

170
00:16:44,247 --> 00:16:45,737
Leave your brother alone.

171
00:16:45,887 --> 00:16:49,937
Andreu is ours now and
he'll stay here as long as he needs.

172
00:16:50,087 --> 00:16:53,455
Florència has to work all day
and hold the fort.

173
00:16:53,607 --> 00:16:55,257
No, it's like this!

174
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:57,296
Quirze, say hi to your cousin.

175
00:16:57,447 --> 00:17:00,291
- Hey. How are you?
- OK.

176
00:17:00,447 --> 00:17:02,734
And don't you remember Nuria?

177
00:17:02,887 --> 00:17:05,697
How could he if Fonso
spent half his life in Manlleu?

178
00:17:05,847 --> 00:17:07,975
Nuria came to live here recently.

179
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:11,776
Andreu's going to stay with us
a while.

180
00:17:22,007 --> 00:17:23,771
And a hello for aunt Enriqueta?

181
00:17:23,927 --> 00:17:25,929
Come here, handsome!

182
00:17:27,127 --> 00:17:29,175
- You're so grown-up!
- You coming with us?

183
00:17:29,327 --> 00:17:32,012
Not yet.
We'll go talk to the teacher tomorrow.

184
00:17:32,167 --> 00:17:34,090
Come on, off to school.

185
00:17:37,127 --> 00:17:39,573
- What's wrong with her hand?
- None of your business.

186
00:17:39,727 --> 00:17:40,694
Cio.

187
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:45,097
A bomb exploded when she was playing
by the river and she lost her fingers.

188
00:17:45,247 --> 00:17:49,491
But don't mention it to her.
She doesn't like to talk about it.

189
00:17:49,927 --> 00:17:50,894
I'll be late today.

190
00:17:51,047 --> 00:17:54,608
All of Vic teamed up
to come have their clothes made.

191
00:17:56,127 --> 00:17:59,290
Now go say goodbye to your father.

192
00:18:20,727 --> 00:18:22,331
Look, Andreu,

193
00:18:23,287 --> 00:18:26,609
I won't be around now
and people are evil.

194
00:18:27,927 --> 00:18:29,975
Always hold your head high.

195
00:18:30,127 --> 00:18:33,176
And if they say ugly things about
me or our family,

196
00:18:33,327 --> 00:18:34,738
pay them no mind.

197
00:18:36,447 --> 00:18:38,256
Everything I'm doing is for you.

198
00:18:40,327 --> 00:18:42,853
What's all the nodding mean?

199
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:44,931
It means me too, father.

200
00:18:50,247 --> 00:18:53,330
PORTRAIT OF A BIRD KILLER

201
00:18:53,487 --> 00:18:55,808
"Victory is never neutral

202
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,298
or undeserved.

203
00:18:57,447 --> 00:18:59,415
Victory

204
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:02,129
is never neutral

205
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:05,213
or undeserved.

206
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:08,810
You must avoid the defeated...

207
00:19:09,607 --> 00:19:11,769
You must avoid

208
00:19:11,927 --> 00:19:14,168
the defeated..."

209
00:19:14,327 --> 00:19:15,488
Shit!

210
00:19:15,647 --> 00:19:19,493
"...like you would the plague".

211
00:19:20,927 --> 00:19:22,258
You dropped this.

212
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:25,971
"...like you would

213
00:19:26,447 --> 00:19:27,892
the plague".

214
00:19:28,047 --> 00:19:31,972
"Vae Victis", which means
"Woe betide the defeated!"

215
00:19:33,007 --> 00:19:36,648
The defeated have no right
to even a small footnote

216
00:19:36,807 --> 00:19:38,730
in the great book of history,

217
00:19:39,247 --> 00:19:42,854
because history is always
written by winners.

218
00:19:46,207 --> 00:19:49,814
But I am always in favor
of victors because

219
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:51,969
they're more worthy.
Anyone know why?

220
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:53,250
Me.

221
00:19:54,007 --> 00:19:55,247
They're braver.

222
00:19:55,407 --> 00:19:58,456
No.
Because they've known how to win.

223
00:19:59,847 --> 00:20:04,489
And only those who know
how to win can win.

224
00:20:04,647 --> 00:20:08,857
Like the rich are more worthy
than the poor. Anyone know why?

225
00:20:09,447 --> 00:20:10,812
Their money.

226
00:20:11,527 --> 00:20:13,291
Almost, you're close.

227
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:16,776
What a shitty teacher,
on and on about the same thing.

228
00:20:16,927 --> 00:20:20,136
Mr. Madern is a drunk,
but he's right about what he says.

229
00:20:20,287 --> 00:20:23,609
About what, smarty-pants?
That you're dumber than a fly?

230
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:27,249
That you should avoid
louses like you like the plague.

231
00:20:27,407 --> 00:20:31,093
Then go! Or are you scared to be
in the woods alone, you little rat?

232
00:20:31,247 --> 00:20:35,252
You're the rats!
You reds will end up like Pitorliua,

233
00:20:35,407 --> 00:20:37,694
hiding in a cave like "monsters".

234
00:20:37,847 --> 00:20:39,895
He isn't a monster.
My father told me.

235
00:20:40,047 --> 00:20:41,651
He doesn't know anything.

236
00:20:41,807 --> 00:20:44,731
He became a monster
from being in the cave so long.

237
00:20:44,887 --> 00:20:47,208
You can still see him
run naked in the woods.

238
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:48,414
That's nonsense!

239
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:51,411
- What kind of monster is he?
- A weird bird.

240
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:53,695
Well, half human, half bird,

241
00:20:53,847 --> 00:20:56,657
but one of those birds
you can't tell what it is

242
00:20:56,807 --> 00:20:57,569
until they mate.

243
00:20:57,727 --> 00:20:58,933
You're dumber than dumb.

244
00:20:59,087 --> 00:21:01,897
Sure, I'm not as well trained as you.

245
00:21:02,447 --> 00:21:03,414
What do you mean?

246
00:21:03,567 --> 00:21:05,296
Teacher pays more attention to you.

247
00:21:05,447 --> 00:21:07,211
You're worse than the flu!

248
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:10,928
The teacher who teaches me
tra-la-la-la- la-la-lee,

249
00:21:11,087 --> 00:21:13,738
The teacher who teaches me
is in love with me.

250
00:21:16,767 --> 00:21:19,532
You're a filthy pig and a liar!

251
00:21:21,487 --> 00:21:25,014
You're all useless! Like dogs!
With no mother or father.

252
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:28,933
Nuria, you'll wind up running around
the woods naked like a whore!

253
00:21:30,087 --> 00:21:32,488
Like your aunt Enriqueta
and her bicycle,

254
00:21:32,647 --> 00:21:36,129
