01:04:03,087 --> 01:04:04,532
Pitorliua...

754
01:04:07,567 --> 01:04:08,614
Look,

755
01:04:08,767 --> 01:04:11,691
Dionis, Pauleta's husband.

756
01:04:11,847 --> 01:04:14,293
Look, the other starts with an F...

757
01:04:14,447 --> 01:04:17,815
Francesc or Ferran or...

758
01:04:18,647 --> 01:04:20,092
Or Farriol.

759
01:04:27,927 --> 01:04:30,771
It's dark out.
We should go...

760
01:04:32,407 --> 01:04:33,568
Nuria?

761
01:04:34,807 --> 01:04:36,093
Nuria.

762
01:05:51,327 --> 01:05:53,056
Look at the faggot!

763
01:06:27,047 --> 01:06:28,094
Faggot!

764
01:07:12,087 --> 01:07:13,054
Andreu!

765
01:07:13,967 --> 01:07:14,934
Andreu.

766
01:07:16,647 --> 01:07:19,776
Where are you going like that?
You'll catch cold.

767
01:07:21,647 --> 01:07:24,014
Now what's wrong? What's wrong?

768
01:07:24,847 --> 01:07:27,771
Go get dressed.
We have a permit to see your father.

769
01:07:27,927 --> 01:07:30,294
- I won't go to the prison.
- What's wrong with you?

770
01:07:30,447 --> 01:07:33,178
- I know what he did to Pitorliua.
- What do you know?

771
01:07:33,327 --> 01:07:35,534
Don't pretend.
He castrated him like a pig.

772
01:07:35,687 --> 01:07:37,894
- Says who?
- Pauleta was at the cemetery...

773
01:07:38,047 --> 01:07:41,449
You think you should listen to her?
Don't you see she's nuts?

774
01:07:41,607 --> 01:07:44,770
- And only wants to hurt people?
- Don't lie to me, dammit!

775
01:07:45,447 --> 01:07:46,733
Come here.

776
01:07:50,327 --> 01:07:54,252
Look, Andreu. These years
were hard for your father.

777
01:07:54,527 --> 01:07:57,974
We were living on my pay only
and almost lost the house.

778
01:07:58,127 --> 01:08:00,812
- Dionis offered him a job.
- And that has to do with?

779
01:08:00,967 --> 01:08:02,890
It was to scare him into leaving.

780
01:08:03,047 --> 01:08:05,812
- Mrs. Manubens would pay them.
- To castrate him?

781
01:08:05,967 --> 01:08:09,176
No, just for the hazing with grease.

782
01:08:09,727 --> 01:08:12,173
Thing is, Dionis was a brute and,

783
01:08:12,327 --> 01:08:14,614
God forgive me
for badmouthing the dead,

784
01:08:14,767 --> 01:08:16,576
he was heartless too.

785
01:08:17,567 --> 01:08:20,411
But I swear your father
had nothing to do

786
01:08:20,567 --> 01:08:22,649
with how it all ended.

787
01:08:26,407 --> 01:08:28,057
Don't judge him.

788
01:08:28,807 --> 01:08:31,572
He's suffered so much
seeing me work like a slave,

789
01:08:31,727 --> 01:08:33,377
hearing you want to be a doctor

790
01:08:33,527 --> 01:08:36,417
and not being able
to give us anything.

791
01:08:38,607 --> 01:08:41,008
Maybe your father made mistakes,

792
01:08:41,167 --> 01:08:43,932
but he did it for us,
especially for you.

793
01:08:44,527 --> 01:08:47,212
If you fail him now,
he'll go to pieces.

794
01:09:16,847 --> 01:09:18,975
Look, they're coming out!

795
01:09:31,807 --> 01:09:33,889
Andreu, up you go!

796
01:09:37,967 --> 01:09:41,574
- Is that him? You see him?
- I don't know. I'm not sure.

797
01:09:42,487 --> 01:09:43,727
Come!

798
01:10:14,727 --> 01:10:15,694
How are you?

799
01:10:15,847 --> 01:10:16,894
OK.

800
01:10:18,928 --> 01:10:21,010
- Has your wound healed?
- What?

801
01:10:21,168 --> 01:10:23,216
Your wound. Is it healed?

802
01:10:23,367 --> 01:10:25,290
Yes, yes, it's healed.

803
01:10:25,968 --> 01:10:29,814
I brought you clothes and food.
I gave it to a guard.

804
01:10:30,247 --> 01:10:34,491
Everyone sends their love. They're
fattening a pig for when you get out.

805
01:10:37,088 --> 01:10:39,853
No, Florència.
It's all over.

806
01:10:41,047 --> 01:10:42,378
You hold on.

807
01:10:42,967 --> 01:10:45,174
It will be OK, you'll see.

808
01:10:48,167 --> 01:10:49,498
How's the boy doing?

809
01:10:49,648 --> 01:10:52,970
Fine, he doesn't miss a day of school
and he's doing well.

810
01:10:57,488 --> 01:10:58,694
Give your father a kiss.

811
01:11:04,247 --> 01:11:07,376
Give this to your mother.
Tell her to get it to the Manubens.

812
01:11:12,048 --> 01:11:12,810
Lady!

813
01:11:12,967 --> 01:11:14,651
I'll kick that kid back in place!

814
01:11:14,807 --> 01:11:15,774
Andreu, come!

815
01:11:18,567 --> 01:11:20,171
What did your father give you?

816
01:11:20,327 --> 01:11:21,658
Hide it, hide it.

817
01:12:42,048 --> 01:12:45,018
Mrs. Manubens is very bossy,
right, grandma?

818
01:12:45,488 --> 01:12:48,014
With all that money she can be.

819
01:12:48,167 --> 01:12:50,295
But she looks sad, doesn't she?

820
01:12:50,448 --> 01:12:52,416
I don't think so.

821
01:12:52,567 --> 01:12:56,049
Poor people. They lost a son
not even 1 and never had more.

822
01:12:56,887 --> 01:12:59,936
And this is Pere, her brother.

823
01:13:00,087 --> 01:13:03,057
They made him marry
a woman he didn't love

824
01:13:03,207 --> 01:13:05,335
and sent him to France.

825
01:13:05,687 --> 01:13:07,098
May he be in Heaven.

826
01:13:07,408 --> 01:13:09,934
He could have had everything,
you see.

827
01:13:10,087 --> 01:13:12,613
Whereas we, who have nothing...

828
01:13:12,768 --> 01:13:15,294
well, we're still alive.

829
01:13:26,208 --> 01:13:28,893
- Can I go?
- Wait, we haven't finished.

830
01:13:32,048 --> 01:13:34,733
When you're finished,
come to my room.

831
01:13:34,887 --> 01:13:36,696
- OK.
- I'll be waiting.

832
01:13:38,247 --> 01:13:39,453
Hey, Andreu!

833
01:13:47,207 --> 01:13:49,494
I'd like to know
why all the portraits!

834
01:13:50,007 --> 01:13:53,090
They're only good
to use in obituaries.

835
01:13:54,887 --> 01:13:55,649
Come in.

836
01:14:00,368 --> 01:14:01,449
Sit, sit.

837
01:14:05,648 --> 01:14:09,494
I didn't know your father was in jail.
The Manubens told me.

838
01:14:10,048 --> 01:14:12,619
They asked about you, your ability,

839
01:14:12,768 --> 01:14:15,738
your knowledge, your behavior.

840
01:14:15,888 --> 01:14:19,734
And to ask you if you want them
to take care of your studies,

841
01:14:19,888 --> 01:14:22,095
if you'd like to get a degree.

842
01:14:22,247 --> 01:14:25,057
It seems your father's case
isn't going too well.

843
01:14:25,207 --> 01:14:27,494
My mother said the lawyer will fix it.

844
01:14:27,767 --> 01:14:30,737
Sure, you never know
until the last minute, right?

845
01:14:30,887 --> 01:14:33,538
But they say
that if it doesn't go well,

846
01:14:34,048 --> 01:14:36,972
your mother could get along better.

847
01:14:37,488 --> 01:14:40,856
I mean... without you...
What do you think?

848
01:14:42,208 --> 01:14:43,255
I don't know.

849
01:14:43,408 --> 01:14:45,809
Look, the Manubens
don't have children,

850
01:14:45,968 --> 01:14:47,857
and want to adopt someone.

851
01:14:48,208 --> 01:14:50,210
I already have parents.

852
01:14:52,608 --> 01:14:54,849
Andreu, you have to be sure
about this.

853
01:14:55,008 --> 01:14:56,658
You can continue studying,

854
01:14:56,807 --> 01:15:00,653
or stay here working in the fields
or a factory. That's all there is.

855
01:15:02,407 --> 01:15:03,329
Wait.

856
01:15:05,607 --> 01:15:08,008
- What?
- They've come for Andreu.

857
01:15:15,568 --> 01:15:17,935
That's a very important decision.

858
01:15:18,688 --> 01:15:21,658
Think it over,
it's a good opportunity.

859
01:15:22,327 --> 01:15:26,412
Know that I'm telling you this
because I love you and your cousins.

860
01:15:26,567 --> 01:15:28,376
Well don't love us so much.

861
01:15:30,368 --> 01:15:33,053
Go on, they're waiting for you.

862
01:15:35,527 --> 01:15:36,210
Andreu.

863
01:15:37,728 --> 01:15:40,618
Look, I lost my parents
when I was very young,

864
01:15:41,207 --> 01:15:44,495
so I had to do what I'm doing
and not what I wanted.

865
01:15:44,647 --> 01:15:47,571
If I'd had an opportunity like you,
I'd have taken it.

866
01:15:48,128 --> 01:15:50,734
You're you and I'm me.

867
01:16:03,728 --> 01:16:05,093
- What did he want?
- Nothing.

868
01:16:05,607 --> 01:16:06,972
Andreu, let's go.

869
01:16:07,527 --> 01:16:09,768
- Your mom's waiting for you.
- What's wrong?

870
01:16:09,927 --> 01:16:11,736
She got a permit to go to the jail.

871
01:16:11,888 --> 01:16:13,697
But we went last week.

872
01:16:13,847 --> 01:16:15,611
They're taking him to Barcelona.

873
01:16:15,767 --> 01:16:19,453
Oh, bad sign. It's what they do
with those who don't return.

874
01:16:24,768 --> 01:16:26,338
Are you stupid or what?

875
01:17:44,128 --> 01:17:45,175
Come here.

876
01:17:46,608 --> 01:17:49,817
Come, sit, I'm tired
of sitting all day.

877
01:17:49,968 --> 01:17:52,096
They asked me if you want a priest.

878
01:17:52,247 --> 01:17:56,047
No priests.
They're all leeches and traitors.

879
01:17:56,208 --> 01:17:58,017
- Hey, Andreu?
- Yes.

880
01:18:04,288 --> 01:18:05,733
Know what?

881
01:18:06,727 --> 01:18:09,492
I heard that owl singing
last night,

882
01:18:10,448 --> 01:18:12,815
and knew he was singing for me.

883
01:18:21,607 --> 01:18:23,291
But I'm not sad,

884
01:18:23,447 --> 01:18:25,973
so you shouldn't be either.

885
01:18:30,048 --> 01:18:32,415
We won't see each other again,
will we?

886
01:18:38,967 --> 01:18:40,014
No.

887
01:18:45,207 --> 01:18:47,175
Now, Andreu, listen closely.

888
01:18:47,328 --> 01:18:48,978
We don't have much time.

889
01:18:50,848 --> 01:18:53,374
The war has hurt us all badly.

890
01:18:54,087 --> 01:18:57,375
But the worst part of war
isn't that people go hungry

891
01:18:57,527 --> 01:19:00,974
or have to escape,
or even that they kill us.

892
01:19:02,327 --> 01:19:05,456
The worst part of war is
they make us forget our ideals,

893
01:19:05,607 --> 01:19:08,417
because without ideals
a person is nothing.

894
01:19:10,448 --> 01:19:13,179
So to me the most important thing
is what's here

895
01:19:17,408 --> 01:19:18,694
and in here.

896
01:19:20,087 --> 01:19:23,409
You must protect that like a treasure.

897
01:19:24,448 --> 01:19:25,415
Will you do that?

898
01:19:33,927 --> 01:19:35,736
And now go,

899
01:19:35,927 --> 01:19:39,773
your mom and I have a lot to talk
about before our time runs out.

900
01:19:43,447 --> 01:19:44,972
I brought you something.

901
01:19:59,447 --> 01:20:00,937
To keep you company.

902
01:20:02,727 --> 01:20:04,809
Not much time left for company.

903
01:20:04,967 --> 01:20:08,210
You'd better take him home with you.

904
01:20:10,448 --> 01:20:11,734
Look after him, OK?

905
01:20:16,647 --> 01:20:18,570
And your mother too,

906
01:20:20,327 --> 01:20:22,250
take good care of her.

907
01:21:38,887 --> 01:21:41,174
You have to mourn for a year.

908
01:21:41,527 --> 01:21:43,689
Your mother, the rest of her life.

909
01:22:05,088 --> 01:22:06,419
Poor thing...

910
01:22:10,528 --> 01:22:12,656
Executed like a criminal.

911
01:22:19,527 --> 01:22:22,770
They didn't let me see him
even in his last moment.

912
01:22:23,287 --> 01:22:25,016
Quirze, sit over there.

913
01:22:48,247 --> 01:22:50,011
Don't shed a single tear.

914
01:22:52,487 --> 01:22:54,012
No need to make them feel sorry.

915
01:22:54,167 --> 01:22:55,578
I'm in charge of the funeral.

916
01:22:55,728 --> 01:22:57,537
We had no time to make cards.

917
01:22:57,687 --> 01:23:01,533
Next Sunday we'll hand them out
if they let us do the burial.

918
01:23:01,687 --> 01:23:03,098
Say hello to Macia.

919
01:23:03,248 --> 01:23:06,138
He's letting us bury
your father in his niche.

920
01:23:06,288 --> 01:23:08,495
Or we'd bury him
in the ground like a dog.

921
01:23:08,647 --> 01:23:10,456
You come with me.

922
01:23:17,447 --> 01:23:19,449
What do I tell that poor woman?

923
01:23:19,607 --> 01:23:22,292
Tell her what I told you before.

924
01:23:32,967 --> 01:23:34,776
Damn priest!

925
01:23:35,367 --> 01:23:38,177
- Why isn't he starting?
- I don't know.

926
01:23:39,888 --> 01:23:41,777
What's wrong? We're all here.

927
01:23:41,927 --> 01:23:45,773
The priest says there's no sense
to a funeral for a man

928
01:23:45,927 --> 01:23:49,010
who cursed priests to the end.

929
01:23:49,447 --> 01:23:53,293
- We can pray together if we want.
- To hell with praying!

930
01:23:53,447 --> 01:23:55,415
Andreu, we're leaving.

931
01:23:58,608 --> 01:24:00,929
120 kilos of fat and nothing more!

932
01:24:01,088 --> 01:24:04,092
No room for what you call
Christian charity.

933
01:24:04,247 --> 01:24:06,375
Don't listen to her.
She's crazy.

934
01:24:09,488 --> 01:24:11,217
- Come back!
- I want them to hear me!

935
01:24:11,367 --> 01:24:12,448
Florència. Not now!

936
01:24:20,608 --> 01:24:23,498
- Leave it be!
- I can't. Don't you see I can't?

937
01:24:27,968 --> 01:24:31,529
So he's dead! You're happy now.

938
01:24:32,487 --> 01:24:34,728
Is his death good for anything?

939
01:24:34,928 --> 01:24:38,216
Is not burying him properly
good for anything?

940
01:24:38,407 --> 01:24:40,136
I'll tell you what it's good for.

941
01:24:40,288 --> 01:24:42,859
To trample those who
won't bow down to you.

942
01:24:43,008 --> 01:24:44,089
Don't make me talk.

943
01:24:44,247 --> 01:24:47,012
You should kill me too, next to him.

944
01:24:47,367 --> 01:24:48,732
Aren't I red enough?

945
01:24:48,887 --> 01:24:50,855
Don't mind her.
She's lost her head.

946
01:24:51,008 --> 01:24:53,614
I'm aware of her condition.
We'll talk later.

947
01:24:53,767 --> 01:24:55,929
You ruined my life.
You hear me?

948
01:24:56,087 --> 01:24:58,977
We've done too much for you.
All of you.

949
01:24:59,127 --> 01:25:01,778
Sure! Black bread and red sugar,

950
01:25:01,927 --> 01:25:04,931
with the ration book
and waiting hours in line!

951
01:25:05,088 --> 01:25:06,897
That's all you've given us.

952
01:25:07,047 --> 01:25:09,812
Bread with no soul or virtue; dead,

953
01:25:09,968 --> 01:25:13,575
like all of you, because of
this goddamn war that's killed us all.

954
01:25:13,728 --> 01:25:17,130
All who deserved it.

955
01:25:28,807 --> 01:25:29,774
Mother, let's go.

956
01:25:32,448 --> 01:25:35,213
When you were in
your mother's womb,

957
01:25:35,847 --> 01:25:39,693
they should have thrown her
in the pigs' trough to be eaten alive.

958
01:25:40,167 --> 01:25:42,932
Let's go, we have
no more business here.

959
01:25:45,847 --> 01:25:46,450
Let's go.

960
01:26:19,168 --> 01:26:20,693
Pauleta, why are you here?

961
01:26:20,848 --> 01:26:22,657
To offer my condolences.

962
01:26:22,807 --> 01:26:25,287
Andreu, go put the cages on the porch.

963
01:26:25,728 --> 01:26:27,014
Let him stay.

964
01:26:27,168 --> 01:26:31,218
Young people need to get
used to hearing serious words.

965
01:26:35,328 --> 01:26:39,652
14 times the judge called me
to ask if I distrusted someone,

966
01:26:39,808 --> 01:26:42,891
if Dionis' death had to do
with Pitorliua...

967
01:26:43,047 --> 01:26:44,970
You have to bring all that up again?

968
01:26:45,127 --> 01:26:47,778
See how they're all dead?
Pitorliua, our husbands. All!

969
01:26:47,927 --> 01:26:51,613
All except Pere Manubens' wife,
who's very much alive.

970
01:26:51,927 --> 01:26:53,850
What are you getting at, Pauleta?

971
01:26:54,007 --> 01:26:55,850
After Pitorliua's misfortune,

972
01:26:56,327 --> 01:26:59,376
Pere went to France,
but they made him marry before.

973
01:26:59,927 --> 01:27:02,976
When he died last year,
his sister, Mrs. Manubens,

974
01:27:03,127 --> 01:27:06,176
told Dionis to steal her brother's
marriage certificate

975
01:27:06,327 --> 01:27:08,807
to nullify the marriage
and keep the entire fortune.

976
01:27:08,967 --> 01:27:11,573
Why don't you tell the judge
and not me?

977
01:27:11,728 --> 01:27:15,210
You can be on the Manubens'
side, but never against them.

978
01:27:16,487 --> 01:27:18,455
I told Dionis that often,

979
01:27:18,608 --> 01:27:20,497
but him,
being so stubborn,

980
01:27:20,647 --> 01:27:23,457
he blackmailed Mrs. Manubens
once he had the papers.

981
01:27:23,607 --> 01:27:26,292
And the damn bitch got rid of him.

982
01:27:27,088 --> 01:27:28,817
Like she did with your man.

983
01:27:30,967 --> 01:27:33,049
Farriol was executed for being red.

984
01:27:33,207 --> 01:27:37,053
Farriol was garroted because
he had no red left in him.

985
01:27:37,527 --> 01:27:39,256
He was like my man:

986
01:27:39,408 --> 01:27:42,139
A lout, a traitor
and a hired killer...

987
01:27:42,288 --> 01:27:43,733
but worse,

988
01:27:44,087 --> 01:27:46,977
because Dionis, despite what he was,

989
01:27:47,127 --> 01:27:49,368
could never have killed a boy.

990
01:27:49,968 --> 01:27:51,015
What do you mean?

991
01:27:51,168 --> 01:27:52,579
Shall I spell it out for you?

992
01:27:52,727 --> 01:27:55,697
Tell you who they paid
this time to finish it all off?

993
01:27:55,847 --> 01:27:57,053
That I won't tolerate!

994
01:27:57,207 --> 01:27:59,858
Yes you will tolerate it!
I owe it to my son!

995
01:28:06,967 --> 01:28:08,173
Get out!

996
01:28:11,047 --> 01:28:14,733
Your father,
always talking about ideals.

997
01:28:14,887 --> 01:28:16,810
Look what shitty ideals he had.

998
01:28:16,967 --> 01:28:17,968
I said get out!

999
01:28:25,767 --> 01:28:28,771
What I don't understand
is Farriol's silence.

1000
01:28:28,928 --> 01:28:31,818
With nothing to lose,
it's like he let himself be killed.

1001
01:28:32,448 --> 01:28:36,294
Pauleta, you gave us your condolences.
You can leave.

1002
01:28:39,168 --> 01:28:40,499
And don't ever come back.

1003
01:28:40,647 --> 01:28:43,537
Good night!
Now go to sleep if you can.

1004
01:28:57,728 --> 01:29:00,254
How could father kill Culet?

1005
01:29:00,487 --> 01:29:02,057
Forgive us, Andreu.

1006
01:29:03,207 --> 01:29:05,528
You have to forgive
your father and I.

1007
01:29:06,848 --> 01:29:08,850
We didn't know how to do a better job.

1008
01:29:09,088 --> 01:29:10,374
Don't touch me!

1009
01:30:53,937 --> 01:30:56,229
No more ghosts, huh?

1010
01:31:03,687 --> 01:31:05,815
Why'd you take off
the mourning bracelet?

1011
01:31:07,127 --> 01:31:10,609
I won't have anything to do
with my father. Or my mother.

1012
01:31:15,927 --> 01:31:17,929
Aunt Cio wants me to work
at the factory.

1013
01:31:18,087 --> 01:31:20,010
The Manubens want
to take me to Igualada.

1014
01:31:20,688 --> 01:31:21,894
They want to hook you.

1015
01:31:24,368 --> 01:31:27,656
Listen, Andreu, why don't we
run away together?

1016
01:31:28,407 --> 01:31:30,216
Us two? Where?

1017
01:31:30,368 --> 01:31:32,052
To Vic, on the train.

1018
01:31:32,208 --> 01:31:34,893
Nobody knows us there.
What do you think?

1019
01:31:36,768 --> 01:31:38,418
I've thought about it a lot.

1020
01:31:38,567 --> 01:31:40,968
We'll set fires in town
at siesta time.

1021
01:31:41,127 --> 01:31:44,609
When they're all running
to put them out, we'll escape.

1022
01:31:47,687 --> 01:31:49,177
Let's make a pact?

1023
01:31:52,608 --> 01:31:53,450
Deal.

1024
01:31:54,727 --> 01:31:57,571
But before, we'll cast a spell.

1025
01:31:58,368 --> 01:32:01,258
And here's the rabbit.
Made with onions as you like it.

1026
01:32:01,408 --> 01:32:03,775
- Now that is a sin!
- You deserve the best.

1027
01:32:03,927 --> 01:32:05,531
You're so understanding with us.

1028
01:32:05,687 --> 01:32:06,574
Forget it...

1029
01:32:06,727 --> 01:32:09,776
Come in. The Manubens
were just talking about you.

1030
01:32:09,927 --> 01:32:13,409
How you and your mother
suffered with your father's death.

1031
01:32:13,568 --> 01:32:16,048
But that's all over, right son?

1032
01:32:18,368 --> 01:32:20,735
Here, this is for you.

1033
01:32:21,408 --> 01:32:22,375
Chocolate.

1034
01:32:23,648 --> 01:32:24,649
Thank you.

1035
01:32:25,088 --> 01:32:27,853
We think you could
help out your mother.

1036
01:32:28,288 --> 01:32:31,337
Another mouth at home
is always a burden,

1037
01:32:31,927 --> 01:32:34,055
especially with no wages.

1038
01:32:34,208 --> 01:32:38,008
Would you like to start high
school next year in Igualada?

1039
01:32:38,167 --> 01:32:39,851
Later you could get a degree.

1040
01:32:40,007 --> 01:32:42,931
Your mother would have
no expenses or headaches.

1041
01:32:43,088 --> 01:32:46,774
And you'd have space to study
and everything at home.

1042
01:32:47,447 --> 01:32:48,972
For God's sake,
say something.

1043
01:32:50,487 --> 01:32:54,094
Leave him, Cio, it's logical
he has to think about it.

1044
01:32:54,688 --> 01:32:57,089
It's good he hasn't had
his wings clipped.

1045
01:32:57,248 --> 01:33:00,013
It will be like now,
Andreu, but different.

1046
01:33:00,167 --> 01:33:02,329
You and your mother think about it.

1047
01:33:02,487 --> 01:33:04,489
We've already discussed it.

1048
01:33:05,408 --> 01:33:06,375
Come here.

1049
01:33:07,767 --> 01:33:11,294
She'll do what you say,
whatever's best for you.

1050
01:33:23,127 --> 01:33:25,528
We'll sign him up
so he won't lose his place

1051
01:33:26,128 --> 01:33:27,937
and later he'll say yes.

1052
01:33:29,648 --> 01:33:30,854
What are you doing?

1053
01:33:31,328 --> 01:33:32,978
I buried two serins.

1054
01:33:33,127 --> 01:33:35,175
- You buried them alive?
- So what?

1055
01:33:35,328 --> 01:33:38,138
You kill them too.
You think we didn't know?

1056
01:33:41,648 --> 01:33:42,809
Look.

1057
01:33:43,968 --> 01:33:46,175
And what did you bring of yours?

1058
01:33:51,968 --> 01:33:53,208
What's so funny?

1059
01:33:53,367 --> 01:33:57,133
- This shitty globe.
- What should they have put there?

1060
01:33:57,728 --> 01:34:01,369
Don't you like birds?
Then lots of birds.

1061
01:34:01,607 --> 01:34:03,848
Dead, stuffed.

1062
01:34:04,007 --> 01:34:07,728
That would be your portrait:
portrait of a bird killer.

1063
01:34:11,687 --> 01:34:13,610
When the bomb blew off my hand,

1064
01:34:13,767 --> 01:34:17,567
the gang gathered all the
little pieces in a shoe box

1065
01:34:18,208 --> 01:34:19,972
and one day I went to get it.

1066
01:34:21,527 --> 01:34:24,053
Dead hand, dead hand,

1067
01:34:24,327 --> 01:34:25,772
knock on this door.

1068
01:34:25,927 --> 01:34:27,338
Leave me alone.

1069
01:34:27,687 --> 01:34:29,610
There's just no kidding with you.

1070
01:34:29,927 --> 01:34:31,452
You know what?

1071
01:34:32,128 --> 01:34:35,018
I'd like to set a bird on fire
one day.

1072
01:34:35,248 --> 01:34:37,933
A ball of fire flying in the air,

1073
01:34:38,247 --> 01:34:41,171
squawking,
until it falls to the ground.

1074
01:34:41,687 --> 01:34:44,418
A shower of ashes is all
that would be left of it.

1075
01:34:48,567 --> 01:34:50,217
Did you ever want to die?

1076
01:34:51,207 --> 01:34:54,177
Well I'll never die completely;

1077
01:34:54,448 --> 01:34:56,610
I'll die little by little,

1078
01:34:56,807 --> 01:34:59,094
first one hand, then the other...

1079
01:34:59,248 --> 01:35:01,569
Remember I'm already a little buried.

1080
01:35:01,728 --> 01:35:04,971
And when I'm really dead,
to hell with the living!

1081
01:35:05,888 --> 01:35:08,255
Dead hand, dead hand,

1082
01:35:09,968 --> 01:35:11,697
Now I can't ever die.

1083
01:35:11,968 --> 01:35:13,208
You're crazy!

1084
01:35:29,207 --> 01:35:30,208
What's that?

1085
01:35:30,368 --> 01:35:33,372
Chocolate. For you.
The owners gave it to me.

1086
01:35:33,527 --> 01:35:34,414
What do they want?

1087
01:35:35,568 --> 01:35:38,174
To go with them to
continue my education.

1088
01:35:38,688 --> 01:35:41,737
- That's what you wanted.
- I want to get my own life together.

1089
01:35:41,888 --> 01:35:43,299
What are you going to do?

1090
01:35:43,447 --> 01:35:47,532
Run away! With my cousin. But first
we're going to burn everything.

1091
01:35:48,048 --> 01:35:49,652
You be careful, Andreu!

1092
01:35:49,808 --> 01:35:52,971
That girl's mad at the world.
And she's evil-minded.

1093
01:35:53,127 --> 01:35:57,257
What should I do? Go to the factory?
With the owners?

1094
01:35:57,607 --> 01:35:59,291
You fly too low, Andreu.

1095
01:35:59,447 --> 01:36:01,973
So low it seems
like you're just walking.

1096
01:36:02,288 --> 01:36:05,053
Fly high and don't let
anyone catch you.

1097
01:36:05,367 --> 01:36:07,210
And how can I do that?

1098
01:36:07,367 --> 01:36:10,689
Thinking. With your head.
And choosing what you like most.

1099
01:36:13,211 --> 01:36:14,586
Then come with me.

1100
01:36:16,128 --> 01:36:17,254
I can't.

1101
01:36:17,568 --> 01:36:18,979
Why can't you?

1102
01:36:20,208 --> 01:36:23,610
Because one of these days
I'll spread my wings,

1103
01:36:23,767 --> 01:36:26,247
spread them wide, completely.

1104
01:36:31,607 --> 01:36:33,018
Don't come any closer.

1105
01:36:54,487 --> 01:36:56,296
- Where were you?
- Around.

1106
01:36:56,688 --> 01:36:58,497
Your mother's waiting for you.

1107
01:36:58,647 --> 01:37:01,014
She came for the thing
with the Manubens.

1108
01:37:13,008 --> 01:37:14,658
Andreu, come in!

1109
01:37:14,807 --> 01:37:15,854
It all went well.

1110
01:37:16,128 --> 01:37:19,018
The owners and your mother agree.
Right, Florència?

1111
01:37:19,168 --> 01:37:22,092
Of course, poor thing can barely
stand up straight.

1112
01:37:22,247 --> 01:37:24,614
We've discussed it.
What's so bad about it?

1113
01:37:25,408 --> 01:37:28,298
All your life moaning about
the owners' conditions,

1114
01:37:28,448 --> 01:37:29,813
now you agree to everything.

1115
01:37:29,968 --> 01:37:32,050
With him it's different.
An education.

1116
01:37:32,208 --> 01:37:34,575
They'll take him away
like he was livestock!

1117
01:37:34,928 --> 01:37:36,089
What should we do?

1118
01:37:36,247 --> 01:37:38,454
Get out of this land that's not ours.

1119
01:37:38,608 --> 01:37:41,817
- So now we have to leave?
- Shut up or you'll get slapped.

1120
01:37:42,768 --> 01:37:44,179
Look, Enriqueta,

1121
01:37:44,327 --> 01:37:47,854
in what stuffy apt. In what
lousy town would we all fit,

1122
01:37:48,007 --> 01:37:50,533
animals, old folks,
aunts, uncles, etc?

1123
01:37:50,688 --> 01:37:53,294
Here even those who
had nothing have eaten.

1124
01:37:53,447 --> 01:37:55,097
I've worked like mad to help.

1125
01:37:55,248 --> 01:37:58,570
When it suited you, with
the schedule and life you wanted.

1126
01:37:58,727 --> 01:38:00,491
We should have bridled you before!

1127
01:38:00,647 --> 01:38:02,331
Do what you will with the boy,

1128
01:38:02,487 --> 01:38:05,809
I won't be at your orders waiting
for a groom on a plate.

1129
01:38:05,968 --> 01:38:08,892
I'll pick him and if he knows
how to raise my skirt, better.

1130
01:38:09,047 --> 01:38:12,017
Stop it!
We're here to talk about Andreu.

1131
01:38:13,808 --> 01:38:15,378
What do you say, mother?

1132
01:38:16,007 --> 01:38:20,296
I can't understand anyone leaving
his village and family,

1133
01:38:20,528 --> 01:38:22,132
but if it's for his own good...

1134
01:38:22,288 --> 01:38:23,699
What about me?

1135
01:38:24,487 --> 01:38:26,888
No one's going to ask me?

1136
01:38:29,488 --> 01:38:31,729
Wasn't I supposed to choose?

1137
01:38:32,688 --> 01:38:34,099
Andreu's right.

1138
01:38:35,248 --> 01:38:36,898
Say what you think, son.

1139
01:38:37,047 --> 01:38:40,847
I don't want to live like this
or be pointed at or more lies.

1140
01:38:41,207 --> 01:38:43,289
I don't want to be like you.

1141
01:38:44,327 --> 01:38:45,613
Come with me.

1142
01:38:51,168 --> 01:38:54,570
We'll do what you want, son,
but I want to be sure

1143
01:38:54,727 --> 01:38:58,129
you realize the people
who want to be your parents are...

1144
01:38:58,288 --> 01:38:59,858
- Do you realize?
- Yes.

1145
01:39:00,007 --> 01:39:02,897
I know it's their fault father's dead.

1146
01:39:11,008 --> 01:39:12,658
Andreu is leaving.

1147
01:39:13,008 --> 01:39:14,851
His father would have wanted it.

1148
01:39:15,008 --> 01:39:17,773
No, mother.
It's what I want.

1149
01:39:23,168 --> 01:39:25,489
You traitor! You promised me.

1150
01:39:26,247 --> 01:39:27,976
How can you leave me alone?

1151
01:39:28,128 --> 01:39:30,813
If I can leave my mother,
why wouldn't I leave you?

1152
01:39:47,168 --> 01:39:48,579
Put that in here.

1153
01:39:50,808 --> 01:39:52,173
So, ready to go?

1154
01:39:53,688 --> 01:39:57,056
If you forgot something,
we'll stop back to get it.

1155
01:39:57,888 --> 01:40:00,494
Now go say goodbye to your family.

1156
01:40:13,048 --> 01:40:16,336
...Polyphemus in "The Odyssey"
represents what is monstrous

1157
01:40:16,487 --> 01:40:19,855
because it only has
one eye and is a giant.

1158
01:40:20,007 --> 01:40:22,214
Also, and this is important,

1159
01:40:22,727 --> 01:40:26,254
because its human nature
was corrupted

1160
01:40:26,407 --> 01:40:28,535
until becoming a being

1161
01:40:28,687 --> 01:40:31,611
of a nature different
from the one it had

1162
01:40:31,768 --> 01:40:33,338
or that was hidden within...

1163
01:40:34,087 --> 01:40:34,690
Yes?

1164
01:40:34,848 --> 01:40:36,418
Visit for Andres Manubens.

1165
01:40:49,208 --> 01:40:51,210
You, face the wall!

1166
01:41:21,607 --> 01:41:24,053
How are you? So, studying a lot?

1167
01:41:24,207 --> 01:41:26,175
- Do they treat you OK?
- Yes, very well.

1168
01:41:26,328 --> 01:41:28,137
I want no complaints about you.

1169
01:41:28,288 --> 01:41:31,371
Show them we taught you well,
you have good manners.

1170
01:41:32,327 --> 01:41:33,897
You can sit, mother.

1171
01:41:35,887 --> 01:41:39,733
I brought you sausage
and everything you like.

1172
01:41:39,887 --> 01:41:42,015
I had to change shifts at the factory,

1173
01:41:42,168 --> 01:41:44,535
change trains, take 2 buses.
You have no idea.

1174
01:41:44,687 --> 01:41:47,054
If it's so hard, don't come anymore.

1175
01:41:49,208 --> 01:41:50,937
That's not why I said it, silly.

1176
01:41:54,168 --> 01:41:56,170
You feel that's the way to treat me?

1177
01:42:00,047 --> 01:42:01,697
You know, Andreu?

1178
01:42:02,208 --> 01:42:04,939
I wish things
had gone differently too.

1179
01:42:05,088 --> 01:42:08,809
I swear I've worked myself
to the bone.

1180
01:42:09,807 --> 01:42:13,254
I've done nothing but
work and work for you

1181
01:42:13,408 --> 01:42:15,456
for your father... for everyone.

1182
01:42:18,328 --> 01:42:20,410
And I will till the day I die...

1183
01:42:21,447 --> 01:42:23,734
I'll cover my own face
with the sheet

1184
01:42:23,887 --> 01:42:26,413
just so I won't have
to trouble anyone.

1185
01:42:29,888 --> 01:42:33,210
Your dad would be so happy
to see you here, so many books.

1186
01:42:33,368 --> 01:42:34,858
Forget about father.

1187
01:42:44,487 --> 01:42:46,410
I have to get back to class.

1188
01:43:05,607 --> 01:43:06,813
You like being here?

1189
01:43:08,608 --> 01:43:10,770
Yes. I like it a lot.

1190
01:43:11,808 --> 01:43:14,937
I want you to know
you're here thanks to him.

1191
01:43:15,488 --> 01:43:18,970
Remember the letter he gave you
in prison for the Manubens?

1192
01:43:19,727 --> 01:43:23,652
It said he wouldn't report them if
they gave you everything you need.

1193
01:43:24,568 --> 01:43:25,933
You understand?

1194
01:43:27,288 --> 01:43:30,371
He let himself be killed
so you could be here.

1195
01:43:33,447 --> 01:43:36,053
I've forgiven your father.

1196
01:43:37,208 --> 01:43:39,734
Maybe you should
forgive him too.

1197
01:44:26,168 --> 01:44:27,772
- Hey, Andreu!
- What?

1198
01:44:27,928 --> 01:44:29,339
Who was that weird woman?

1199
01:44:29,487 --> 01:44:32,377
Someone from my town
with a package for me.